articles.author: TERRY SPENCER and HAVEN DALEY
articles.description: TAMPA, Fla. (AP) — Steady rain fell and winds began to gust in the Tampa Bay area Wednesday morning as a mighty Hurricane Milton churned toward a potentially catastrophic collision with the west coast of Florida, where officials sounded urgent warnings for residents to flee inland or face grim odds of surviving the storm's surge.
articles.title: Time to evacuate is running out as Hurricane Milton closes in on Florida

articles.author: SAMY MAGDY and WAFAA SHURAFA
articles.description: DEIR AL-BALAH, Gaza Strip (AP) — A large-scale Israeli operation in northern Gaza has killed dozens of people and threatens to shut down three hospitals over a year into the war with Hamas, Palestinian officials and residents said Wednesday.
articles.title: Israeli offensive in hard-hit northern Gaza kills dozens and threatens hospitals

articles.author: ZEKE MILLER, TIA GOLDENBERG and AAMER MADHANI
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — President Joe Biden and Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu on Wednesday held their first call in seven weeks, a conversation that comes as Israel expands its ground incursion into Lebanon and considers how to respond to Iran’s recent ballistic missile attack.
articles.title: Biden and Netanyahu hold their first conversation in weeks. Trump recently called the Israeli leader

articles.author: DAVID BAUDER
articles.description: NEW YORK (AP) — Nearly a decade into the Trump Era of politics, less than a month from his third Election Day as the Republican candidate for president and there is still remarkably little consensus within the media about how best to cover Donald Trump.
articles.title: Sanewashing? The banality of crazy? A decade into the Trump era, media hasn't figured him out

articles.author: WILL WEISSERT
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Donald Trump is holding rallies on Wednesday in pivotal Pennsylvania while Vice President Kamala Harris prepares for another visit to the West — even as Hurricane Milton menaces Florida and threatens to overshadow presidential campaigning.
articles.title: Trump sets sights on Pennsylvania and Harris plans to head west as hurricane scrambles campaigning

articles.author: FATIMA HUSSEIN
articles.description: WASHINGTON (AP) — Sherri Myers, an 82-year-old resident of Pensacola City, Florida, says the Social Security cost-of-living increase she'll receive in January “won't make a dent” in helping her meet her day-to-day expenses.
articles.title: Social Security's scheduled cost of living increase 'won't make a dent' for some retirees

articles.author: SCOTT BAUER
articles.description: MADISON, Wis. (AP) — Justices on the Wisconsin Supreme Court said Wednesday that Gov. Tony Evers' creative use of his expansive veto power in an attempt to lock in a school funding increase for 400 years appeared to be “extreme” and “crazy" but questioned whether and how it should be reigned in.
articles.title: Wisconsin Supreme Court grapples with governor's 400-year veto, calling it 'crazy'

articles.author: EVENS SANON and PIERRE-RICHARD LUXAMA
articles.description: PONT-SONDÉ, Haiti (AP) — The death toll in a brutal gang attack last week on a small town in central Haiti has risen to 115, a local official told The Associated Press on Wednesday.The attack on residents of Pont-Sondé on Oct.
articles.title: The death toll in a gang attack on a small Haitian town rises to 115, a local official says

articles.author: DANIEL NIEMANN, MIKE CORDER and CHRISTINA LARSON
articles.description: STOCKHOLM (AP) — Three scientists who discovered powerful techniques to predict and even design novel proteins — the building blocks of life — were awarded the Nobel Prize in chemistry on Wednesday.
articles.title: Nobel Prize in chemistry awarded to 3 scientists for work on proteins, building blocks of life
